  "prompt": "How do you repair the sole of a shoe?",
  "response": "Here are some methods to repair shoe soles:\n\n1. For minor damage:\n- Use shoe glue or shoe repair adhesive\n- Clean the damaged area thoroughly\n- Apply glue evenly\n- Clamp or press the sole while drying\n- Allow 24 hours to cure\n\n2. For small holes:\n- Use a shoe repair patch\n- Cut patch to match hole size\n- Apply strong adhesive\n- Press patch firmly\n- Allow to dry completely\n\n3. For significant damage:\n- Use a shoe repair kit\n- Sand down the damaged area\n- Apply repair compound\n- Let dry and sand smooth\n- Reattach sole if necessary\n\n4. Professional methods:\n- Resoling by a cobbler\n- Complete sole replacement\n- Stitching or vulcanizing\n\n5. For rubber soles:\n- Use rubber cement\n- Clean surface\n- Apply cement\n- Press and hold\n- Allow proper drying time\n\n6. Preventative tips:\n- Use waterproof sealant\n- Address damage early\n- Rotate shoes\n- Store properly\n\nChoose method based on:\n- Extent of damage\n- Shoe material\n- Your skill level\n- Cost of professional repair",
